article.headline: Bonvicini now 525-204 overall at two schools
article.linkText: Bonvicini wins her 200th game for No. 20 Arizona
article.story:
TUCSON, Ariz. (AP) -- Joan Bonvicini won her 200th game with
Arizona, and Shawtinice Polk had 16 points and 11 rebounds as the
No. 20 Wildcats defeated Oregon 96-65 Thursday night.

	   Bonvicini improved to 200-133 in 12 years at Arizona and 525-204
overall. She coached at Long Beach State for 12 seasons before
turning around the Arizona program.

	   The Wildcats (8-3, 2-1) built a 19-point first-half lead behind
Polk, who scored 14 points in the opening 10 minutes. Polk finished
with her ninth double-double of the season.

	   Krista Warren had 18 points and nine rebounds for Arizona.

	   Oregon (5-7, 1-2) got 19 points from Carolyn Ganes, while Andrea
Bills and Kayla Steen added 11 apiece.

	   Arizona pulled ahead with a 21-2 run midway through the first
half. The Wildcats scored most of their first-half points in the
paint and shot 57 percent from the floor.

	   The Wildcats led 43-29 at halftime.

	   Arizona relied on its perimeter shooting in the second half,
making eight of 12 3-pointers.
